                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/713: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-06T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 6, 1938—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>502. For Rublee. Your 856, September 2, 4 p.m. Weddell telegraphs:</p>
                <p>[Here follows paraphrase of telegram No. 252, September 5, 9 p.m., <hi
                        rend="italic">supra.</hi>]</p>
                <p>Before instructing him to press the matter further we would appreciate any
                    comment you may wish to make.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
